#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn47.43"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.43:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.43:0.2"
msgid "5. Amatavagga "
msgstr "5. The Deathless "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn47.43:0.3"
msgid "43. Maggasutta "
msgstr "43. The Path "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.185, sc1
msgctxt "sn47.43:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.43:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants: "

msgctxt "sn47.43:1.3"
msgid "“ekamidāhaṃ, bhikkhave, samayaṃ uruvelāyaṃ viharāmi najjā nerañjarāya tīre ajapālanigrodhe paṭhamābhisambuddho. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, at one time, when I was first awakened, I was staying near Uruvelā at the goatherd’s banyan tree on the bank of the Nerañjarā River. "

msgctxt "sn47.43:1.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr "As I was in private retreat this thought came to mind: "

msgctxt "sn47.43:1.5"
msgid "‘ekāyanvāyaṃ maggo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā sokaparidevānaṃ samatikkamāya dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa sacchikiriyāya, yadidaṃ—cattāro satipaṭṭhānā. "
msgstr "‘The four kinds of mindfulness meditation are the path to convergence. They are in order to purify sentient beings, to get past sorrow and crying, to make an end of pain and sadness, to end the cycle of suffering, and to realize extinguishment.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn47.43:2.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn47.43:2.2"
msgid "Kāye vā bhikkhu kāyānupassī vihareyya ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ; "
msgstr "A mendicant would meditate observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.43:2.3"
msgid "vedanāsu vā bhikkhu vedanānupassī vihareyya … pe … "
msgstr "Or they’d meditate observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "sn47.43:2.4"
msgid "citte vā bhikkhu cittānupassī vihareyya … pe … "
msgstr "or mind … "

msgctxt "sn47.43:2.5"
msgid "dhammesu vā bhikkhu dhammānupassī vihareyya ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "or principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.43:2.6"
msgid "Ekāyanvāyaṃ maggo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā sokaparidevānaṃ samatikkamāya dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa sacchikiriyāya, yadidaṃ—cattāro satipaṭṭhānā’ti. "
msgstr "The four kinds of mindfulness meditation are the path to convergence. They are in order to purify sentient beings, to get past sorrow and crying, to make an end of pain and sadness, to end the cycle of suffering, and to realize extinguishment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.186, sc3
msgctxt "sn47.43:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, brahmā sahampati mama cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—brahmaloke antarahito mama purato pāturahosi. "
msgstr "And then Brahmā Sahampati, knowing what I was thinking, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, vanished from the Brahmā realm and reappeared in front of me. "

msgctxt "sn47.43:3.2"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, brahmā sahampati ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yenāhaṃ tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā maṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "He arranged his robe over one shoulder, knelt on his right knee, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said: "

msgctxt "sn47.43:3.3"
msgid "‘evametaṃ, bhagavā, evametaṃ, sugata. "
msgstr "‘That’s so true, Blessed One! That’s so true, Holy One! "

msgctxt "sn47.43:3.4"
msgid "Ekāyanvāyaṃ, bhante, maggo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā sokaparidevānaṃ samatikkamāya dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa sacchikiriyāya, yadidaṃ—cattāro satipaṭṭhānā. "
msgstr "Sir, the four kinds of mindfulness meditation are the path to convergence. They are in order to purify sentient beings, to get past sorrow and crying, to make an end of pain and sadness, to end the cycle of suffering, and to realize extinguishment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn47.43:4.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn47.43:4.2"
msgid "Kāye vā, bhante, bhikkhu kāyānupassī vihareyya ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ; "
msgstr "A mendicant would meditate observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.43:4.3"
msgid "vedanāsu vā … pe … "
msgstr "Or they’d meditate observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "sn47.43:4.4"
msgid "citte vā … pe … "
msgstr "or mind … "

msgctxt "sn47.43:4.5"
msgid "dhammesu vā, bhante, bhikkhu dhammānupassī vihareyya ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "or principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.43:4.6"
msgid "Ekāyanvāyaṃ, bhante, maggo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā sokaparidevānaṃ samatikkamāya dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa sacchikiriyāya, yadidaṃ—cattāro satipaṭṭhānā’ti. "
msgstr "The four kinds of mindfulness meditation are the path to convergence. They are in order to purify sentient beings, to get past sorrow and crying, to make an end of pain and sadness, to end the cycle of suffering, and to realize extinguishment.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn47.43:5.1"
msgid "Idamavoca, bhikkhave, brahmā sahampati. "
msgstr "That’s what Brahmā Sahampati said. "

msgctxt "sn47.43:5.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvā athāparaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then he went on to say: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn47.43:6.1"
msgid "‘Ekāyanaṃ jātikhayantadassī, "
msgstr "‘The compassionate one, who sees the ending of rebirth, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn47.43:6.2"
msgid "Maggaṃ pajānāti hitānukampī; "
msgstr "understands the path to convergence. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn47.43:6.3"
msgid "Etena maggena tariṃsu pubbe, "
msgstr "By this path people crossed over before, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn47.43:6.4"
msgid "Tarissanti ye ca taranti oghan’”ti. "
msgstr "will cross over, and are crossing over.’” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.43:6.5"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

